pageContext.claim: “Forget about what was on the e-mails, it's irrelevant, although many of them were classified, highly classified and you go to jail for that.”
pageContext.analysis: The Justice Department investigated and decided there was no case for prosecution though Clinton had been careless. Many emails were retroactively classified, but FBI Director James Comey said that “seven email chains concern matters that were classified at the Top Secret/Special Access Program level when they were sent and received. These chains involved Secretary Clinton both sending emails about those matters and receiving emails from others about the same matters.”
